n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":77,"totalLines":77,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1782386882356,"end":1782386882360}},"id":"prt_efe897732001qHKZj7oh04PFhp","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe894db9001NC1iUdANhyeCOb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782386882371,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_da1f97ec85fc4c1a9bf58ea2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. TOPIC\n36: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n41: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n42: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n43: - [ ] [Question 2]\n44: - [ ] [Question 3]\n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n50: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n55: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n60: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n61: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n67: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n68: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n69: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n70: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n71: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n76: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n77: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n78: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n84: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n85: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n86: \n87: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n88: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n89: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n90: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n91: \n92: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n93: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n94: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n100: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n101: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n102: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n103: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n108: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n109: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n110: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n115: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n116: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n117: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n122: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n123: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n128: - Max iterations: [from config]\n129: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n130: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n131: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n132: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n133: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n134: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n135: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n136: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n137: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n138: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n139: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n140: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 140 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":140,"totalLines":140,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1782386882363,"end":1782386882369}},"id":"prt_efe89773a0012ITa7D94n814jn","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe894db9001NC1iUdANhyeCOb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782386882409,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2fdf9c2b49f7465fbda81d1c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-RESEARCH\n2: \n3: # Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n4: \n5: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n6: \n7: ## STATE\n8: \n9: {state_summary}\n10: \n11: Research Topic: {research_topic}\n12: Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n13: Focus Area: {next_focus}\n14: Remaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\n15: Carried-Forward Open Questions:\n16: {carried_forward_open_questions}\n17: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n18: \n19: ## STATE FILES\n20: \n21: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n22: \n23: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n24: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n25: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n26: - Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n27: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n28: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n29: \n30: ## CONSTRAINTS\n31: \n32: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n33: - Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n34: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n35: - The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n36: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n37: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n38: \n39: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n40: \n41: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n42: \n43: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n44: \n45: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n46: \n47: ```json\n48: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n49: ```\n50: \n51: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n52: \n53: For non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n54: \n55: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n56: \n57: Example delta file contents (one iteration):\n58: ```json\n59: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n60: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n61: {\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n62: {\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n63: {\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n64: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n65: ```\n66: \n67: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 67 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-RESEARCH\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nCarried-Forward Open Questions:\n{carried_forward_open_questions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-RESEARCH\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nCarried-Forward Open Questions:\n{carried_forward_open_questions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n```\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\nFor non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n\nExample delta file contents (one iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":67,"totalLines":67,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1782386882403,"end":1782386882407}},"id":"prt_efe8977610013yTG0hNLU2XLq4","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe894db9001NC1iUdANhyeCOb"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782386882876,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"id":"prt_efe89793a001vRP47jGwO4c9Cs","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"236aaadff7f07c95a24e5d4146132301b659a56a","messageID":"msg_efe894db9001NC1iUdANhyeCOb","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":65778,"input":3634,"output":172,"reasoning":20,"cache":{"write":0,"read":61952}},"cost":0.0166004}}
