{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782387150706,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_435552e3ad984ea5bf806e5d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/README.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # design-systems\n2: Build, document, and maintain scalable design systems — from tokens and components to accessibility and theming.\n3: ## Skills (11)\n4: - **design-token** — Define and organize design tokens with naming conventions and usage guidance.\n5: - **component-spec** — Write a detailed component specification including props, states, variants, and accessibility.\n6: - **pattern-library** — Structure a pattern library entry with problem context, solution, and examples.\n7: - **naming-convention** — Establish naming convention systems for design elements, components, and tokens.\n8: - **accessibility-audit** — Conduct an accessibility audit against WCAG guidelines with severity ratings.\n9: - **theming-system** — Design a theming architecture for brand variants, dark mode, and high-contrast.\n10: - **icon-system** — Create an icon system specification covering grid, sizing, naming, and categories.\n11: - **documentation-template** — Generate structured documentation templates for design system artifacts.\n12: - **motion-system** — Define a motion system with duration tokens, easing vocabulary, and reduced-motion handling.\n13: - **design-system-governance** — Define how a design system evolves — contribution models, versioning, change management, and deprecation.\n14: - **localization-design** — Design interfaces that adapt gracefully to multiple languages, writing directions, and cultural contexts.\n15: ## Commands (3)\n16: - `/audit-system` — Audit a design system for consistency, completeness, and accessibility.\n17: - `/create-component` — Scaffold a full component specification from a name or description.\n18: - `/tokenize` — Extract and organize design tokens from an existing design or stylesheet.\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# design-systems\nBuild, document, and maintain scalable design systems — from tokens and components to accessibility and theming.\n## Skills (11)\n- **design-token** — Define and organize design tokens with naming conventions and usage guidance.\n- **component-spec** — Write a detailed component specification including props, states, variants, and accessibility.\n- **pattern-library** — Structure a pattern library entry with problem context, solution, and examples.\n- **naming-convention** — Establish naming convention systems for design elements, components, and tokens.\n- **accessibility-audit** — Conduct an accessibility audit against WCAG guidelines with severity ratings.\n- **theming-system** — Design a theming architecture for brand variants, dark mode, and high-contrast.\n- **icon-system** — Create an icon system specification covering grid, sizing, naming, and categories.\n- **documentation-template** — Generate structured documentation templates for design system artifacts.\n- **motion-system** — Define a motion system with duration tokens, easing vocabulary, and reduced-motion handling.\n- **design-system-governance** — Define how a design system evolves — contribution models, versioning, change management, and deprecation.\n- **localization-design** — Design interfaces that adapt gracefully to multiple languages, writing directions, and cultural contexts.\n## Commands (3)\n- `/audit-system` — Audit a design system for consistency, completeness, and accessibility.\n- `/create-component` — Scaffold a full component specification from a name or description.\n- `/tokenize` — Extract and organize design tokens from an existing design or stylesheet.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/README.md","text":"# design-systems\nBuild, document, and maintain scalable design systems — from tokens and components to accessibility and theming.\n## Skills (11)\n- **design-token** — Define and organize design tokens with naming conventions and usage guidance.\n- **component-spec** — Write a detailed component specification including props, states, variants, and accessibility.\n- **pattern-library** — Structure a pattern library entry with problem context, solution, and examples.\n- **naming-convention** — Establish naming convention systems for design elements, components, and tokens.\n- **accessibility-audit** — Conduct an accessibility audit against WCAG guidelines with severity ratings.\n- **theming-system** — Design a theming architecture for brand variants, dark mode, and high-contrast.\n- **icon-system** — Create an icon system specification covering grid, sizing, naming, and categories.\n- **documentation-template** — Generate structured documentation templates for design system artifacts.\n- **motion-system** — Define a motion system with duration tokens, easing vocabulary, and reduced-motion handling.\n- **design-system-governance** — Define how a design system evolves — contribution models, versioning, change management, and deprecation.\n- **localization-design** — Design interfaces that adapt gracefully to multiple languages, writing directions, and cultural contexts.\n## Commands (3)\n- `/audit-system` — Audit a design system for consistency, completeness, and accessibility.\n- `/create-component` — Scaffold a full component specification from a name or description.\n- `/tokenize` — Extract and organize design tokens from an existing design or stylesheet.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":18,"totalLines":18,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/README.md","time":{"start":1782387150700,"end":1782387150705}},"id":"prt_efe8d8f6a001oVGlbvVSe1pveV","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe8d7dea0017l9gVt5LlGfWth"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782387151557,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f3d9c10345ed4483895827c1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/README.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # interaction-design\n2: Design meaningful interactions with micro-animations, state machines, gestures, error handling, and feedback patterns.\n3: ## Skills (15)\n4: - **micro-interaction-spec** — Specify micro-interactions with trigger, rules, feedback, and loop/mode definitions.\n5: - **animation-principles** — Apply animation principles to UI motion for purposeful, polished interactions.\n6: - **state-machine** — Model complex UI behavior as finite state machines with states and transitions.\n7: - **gesture-patterns** — Design gesture-based interactions for touch and pointer devices.\n8: - **error-handling-ux** — Design error prevention, detection, and recovery experiences.\n9: - **loading-states** — Design loading, skeleton, and progressive content reveal patterns.\n10: - **feedback-patterns** — Design system feedback for user actions including confirmations and status.\n11: - **hicks-law** — Apply Hick's Law to reduce decision time by limiting the number of simultaneous choices presented to users.\n12: - **millers-law** — Apply Miller's Law — chunk information into groups of ~4 to work within working memory limits.\n13: - **fitts-law** — Apply Fitts's Law to size and position interactive targets for fast, accurate interaction.\n14: - **doherty-threshold** — Apply the Doherty Threshold — keep system response times under 400ms to maintain user flow.\n15: - **form-design** — Design forms that minimize friction, prevent errors, and guide users to successful completion.\n16: - **onboarding-design** — Design first-run experiences that get users to value quickly without overwhelming them.\n17: - **navigation-patterns** — Select and design navigation patterns that match product structure, user tasks, and platform conventions.\n18: - **search-ux** — Design search experiences that help users find what they need, recover from failure, and refine results.\n19: ## Commands (3)\n20: - `/design-interaction` — Design a complete interaction flow for a feature or component.\n21: - `/map-states` — Model the states and transitions for a complex UI component.\n22: - `/error-flow` — Design a complete error handling flow for a feature.\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# interaction-design\nDesign meaningful interactions with micro-animations, state machines, gestures, error handling, and feedback patterns.\n## Skills (15)\n- **micro-interaction-spec** — Specify micro-interactions with trigger, rules, feedback, and loop/mode definitions.\n- **animation-principles** — Apply animation principles to UI motion for purposeful, polished interactions.\n- **state-machine** — Model complex UI behavior as finite state machines with states and transitions.\n- **gesture-patterns** — Design gesture-based interactions for touch and pointer devices.\n- **error-handling-ux** — Design error prevention, detection, and recovery experiences.\n- **loading-states** — Design loading, skeleton, and progressive content reveal patterns.\n- **feedback-patterns** — Design system feedback for user actions including confirmations and status.\n- **hicks-law** — Apply Hick's Law to reduce decision time by limiting the number of simultaneous choices presented to users.\n- **millers-law** — Apply Miller's Law — chunk information into groups of ~4 to work within working memory limits.\n- **fitts-law** — Apply Fitts's Law to size and position interactive targets for fast, accurate interaction.\n- **doherty-threshold** — Apply the Doherty Threshold — keep system response times under 400ms to maintain user flow.\n- **form-design** — Design forms that minimize friction, prevent errors, and guide users to successful completion.\n- **onboarding-design** — Design first-run experiences that get users to value quickly without overwhelming them.\n- **navigation-patterns** — Select and design navigation patterns that match product structure, user tasks, and platform conventions.\n- **search-ux** — Design search experiences that help users find what they need, recover from failure, and refine results.\n## Commands (3)\n- `/design-interaction` — Design a complete interaction flow for a feature or component.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/README.md","text":"# interaction-design\nDesign meaningful interactions with micro-animations, state machines, gestures, error handling, and feedback patterns.\n## Skills (15)\n- **micro-interaction-spec** — Specify micro-interactions with trigger, rules, feedback, and loop/mode definitions.\n- **animation-principles** — Apply animation principles to UI motion for purposeful, polished interactions.\n- **state-machine** — Model complex UI behavior as finite state machines with states and transitions.\n- **gesture-patterns** — Design gesture-based interactions for touch and pointer devices.\n- **error-handling-ux** — Design error prevention, detection, and recovery experiences.\n- **loading-states** — Design loading, skeleton, and progressive content reveal patterns.\n- **feedback-patterns** — Design system feedback for user actions including confirmations and status.\n- **hicks-law** — Apply Hick's Law to reduce decision time by limiting the number of simultaneous choices presented to users.\n- **millers-law** — Apply Miller's Law — chunk information into groups of ~4 to work within working memory limits.\n- **fitts-law** — Apply Fitts's Law to size and position interactive targets for fast, accurate interaction.\n- **doherty-threshold** — Apply the Doherty Threshold — keep system response times under 400ms to maintain user flow.\n- **form-design** — Design forms that minimize friction, prevent errors, and guide users to successful completion.\n- **onboarding-design** — Design first-run experiences that get users to value quickly without overwhelming them.\n- **navigation-patterns** — Select and design navigation patterns that match product structure, user tasks, and platform conventions.\n- **search-ux** — Design search experiences that help users find what they need, recover from failure, and refine results.\n## Commands (3)\n- `/design-interaction` — Design a complete interaction flow for a feature or component.\n- `/map-states` — Model the states and transitions for a complex UI component.\n- `/error-flow` — Design a complete error handling flow for a feature.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":22,"totalLines":22,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/README.md","time":{"start":1782387151549,"end":1782387151556}},"id":"prt_efe8d92ba0015ojspIi7RvqgIm","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe8d7dea0017l9gVt5LlGfWth"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782387152402,"sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_88eec97bc649476babeb993a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/visual-critique/README.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/visual-critique/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Visual Critique\n2: \n3: Visual critique skills for designers. Analyse a screen across seven dimensions — hierarchy, brand consistency, composition, typography, colour, affordance, and information density — then compile a prioritised fix list.\n4: \n5: ## Skills\n6: \n7: | Skill | What it does |\n8: |---|---|\n9: | `critique-visual-hierarchy` | Audits entry point, eye flow, weight distribution, and emphasis |\n10: | `critique-brand-consistency` | Checks against `mood.md`, `voice.md`, and `tokens.md` |\n11: | `critique-composition` | Evaluates balance, whitespace, rhythm, and gestalt principles |\n12: | `critique-typography` | Reviews scale usage, readability, consistency, and token compliance |\n13: | `critique-color` | Audits contrast ratios, palette coherence, semantic colour use, and colour accessibility |\n14: | `critique-affordance` | Evaluates clickability signals, state visibility, CTA clarity, and action discoverability |\n15: | `critique-information-density` | Assesses cognitive load, content priority, scanning patterns, and progressive disclosure |\n16: \n17: ## Commands\n18: \n19: | Command | What it does |\n20: |---|---|\n21: | `/critique-screen` | Runs all seven critiques in sequence and outputs a prioritised fix list |\n22: | `/critique-ux` | Focused functional critique: hierarchy, affordance, and information density — for quick loops and PM-led reviews |\n23: \n24: ## Usage\n25: \n26: Run a full screen critique:\n27: ```\n28: /critique-screen onboarding step 2\n29: ```\n30: \n31: Run a focused UX critique (faster, no visual polish dimensions):\n32: ```\n33: /critique-ux checkout step 3\n34: ```\n35: \n36: Or invoke individual skills for targeted feedback:\n37: ```\n38: Use the critique-affordance skill on this screen.\n39: ```\n\n(End of file - total 39 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Visual Critique\n\nVisual critique skills for designers. Analyse a screen across seven dimensions — hierarchy, brand consistency, composition, typography, colour, affordance, and information density — then compile a prioritised fix list.\n\n## Skills\n\n| Skill | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `critique-visual-hierarchy` | Audits entry point, eye flow, weight distribution, and emphasis |\n| `critique-brand-consistency` | Checks against `mood.md`, `voice.md`, and `tokens.md` |\n| `critique-composition` | Evaluates balance, whitespace, rhythm, and gestalt principles |\n| `critique-typography` | Reviews scale usage, readability, consistency, and token compliance |\n| `critique-color` | Audits contrast ratios, palette coherence, semantic colour use, and colour accessibility |\n| `critique-affordance` | Evaluates clickability signals, state visibility, CTA clarity, and action discoverability |\n| `critique-information-density` | Assesses cognitive load, content priority, scanning patterns, and progressive disclosure |\n\n## Commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---|---|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/visual-critique/README.md","text":"# Visual Critique\n\nVisual critique skills for designers. Analyse a screen across seven dimensions — hierarchy, brand consistency, composition, typography, colour, affordance, and information density — then compile a prioritised fix list.\n\n## Skills\n\n| Skill | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `critique-visual-hierarchy` | Audits entry point, eye flow, weight distribution, and emphasis |\n| `critique-brand-consistency` | Checks against `mood.md`, `voice.md`, and `tokens.md` |\n| `critique-composition` | Evaluates balance, whitespace, rhythm, and gestalt principles |\n| `critique-typography` | Reviews scale usage, readability, consistency, and token compliance |\n| `critique-color` | Audits contrast ratios, palette coherence, semantic colour use, and colour accessibility |\n| `critique-affordance` | Evaluates clickability signals, state visibility, CTA clarity, and action discoverability |\n| `critique-information-density` | Assesses cognitive load, content priority, scanning patterns, and progressive disclosure |\n\n## Commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `/critique-screen` | Runs all seven critiques in sequence and outputs a prioritised fix list |\n| `/critique-ux` | Focused functional critique: hierarchy, affordance, and information density — for quick loops and PM-led reviews |\n\n## Usage\n\nRun a full screen critique:\n```\n/critique-screen onboarding step 2\n```\n\nRun a focused UX critique (faster, no visual polish dimensions):\n```\n/critique-ux checkout step 3\n```\n\nOr invoke individual skills for targeted feedback:\n```\nUse the critique-affordance skill on this screen.\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":39,"totalLines":39,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/visual-critique/README.md","time":{"start":1782387152393,"end":1782387152400}},"id":"prt_efe8d960700173d1nE9ou3yuHK","sessionID":"ses_1017781abffe8Jf4LLgGRFccm9","messageID":"msg_efe8d7dea0017l9gVt5LlGfWth"}}
